<br>
We were given items by Verant to give to pets to make them stronger and better. Chaincasting does not allow this. Therefore, why would we try to get all those swords, and belts, etc if we are not going to use them and keep pets alive?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Verant also gave us tools to make chaining better as well. Improved Reclaim, Quick Summoning, Elemental Pact, and even the one shot Frenzied Burnout help chainers.  The new pets naturally make chaining more efficient, costing no more mana than a Greater Vocarate.  We have Burnout 5, also costing no more mana than Burnout 3.<br>
<br>
As far as the &quot;one track mind&quot; comment, pet tank/mag nuke has been the standby tactic of every magician, myself included, from the time we reached level 4 and summoned our very first pet.  It's old.  It's inefficient.  It's all about mana pool, and how many nukes/heals you can get off before you are oom and running.  I don't know about most casters, but oom is not a place I want to be.<br>
<br>
That being said, I totally agree that magician soloing in the new zones has been more than just a little disappointing.  It has forced me to recruit others for groups and apply our talents in coordinated ways in order to accomplish what we used to be able to do without so much assistance.<br>
<br>
The good news is, if there are enough magicians lfg, and appropriately flagged, even a minimum of 2 magicians can group up and take advantage of the XP gold rush that is Tier 2 Planes and beyond.  You can trust me on that one.  I have done it....  over and over again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2629<br> <font color=#333333>(2/7/03 3:15:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=143>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Brainstorm: How to fix PoP Mage soloability</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Once you become 63 those mobs become light blue. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Light blue mobs give xp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=immlazen>Immlazen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#333333>(2/7/03 6:33:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=144>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Brainstorm: How to fix PoP Mage soloability</span><hr size=1> Goladus<br>
