Immlazen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2631<br> <font color=#333333>(2/7/03 7:01:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=145>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Brainstorm: How to fix PoP Mage soloability</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Why are you trying so hard to prove that Mages can solo efficiently? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Several reasons.<br>
<br>
First, Raz asked me some questions and I'm doing my best to answer them.<br>
<br>
Second, I may be misinterpreting you but my argument is closer to &quot;the effeciency with which we can solo is fine,&quot; rather than &quot;mages can solo effeciently.&quot;  The ambiguity of the word &quot;effecient&quot; causes this confusion.<br>
<br>
Third, part of the reason I seem to be as contrary as I do is the extent to which people are pushing to have solo abilities added.  I believe you said something like &quot;that we can solo to 65 is bull @#%$.&quot;  Extreme positions, especially extreme positions that seem prone to exaggeration trigger reactions.  When I percieve something to be an exaggeration I question it, and in that questioning I frequently get misunderstood as being deliberately contrary.<br>
<br>
Fourth, I have said little about the ability to xp 63-64 as I have not been through these levels yet.  With Servant of Marr, Ward of Xegony, and Burnout V to play with I am content to stay 62 and catch on up aa for the time being, and that includes xp gained from light blue mobs.  I prefer soloing dark blues, but light blues in PoP still give what I think is a considerable amount of xp.<br>
<br>
Fifth, I will say this:  Our soloing is risky enough such that with my old p366/geforce2 machine I found it extraordinarily difficult if not impossible to solo in Poop.  Make of that what you will. <p><center><br>
