I've seen the opposite happen. With more pets and adding a slower, the pets last the whole fight, leaving you the mana to nuke, equip the pet, and throw in a heal periodically. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I didn't say add more pets and a slower I just said a slower.  The reason you start nuking in such a situation is because you would otherwise be wasting mana at full.  Unless you will hit full mana, steady chaining will probably be the more effecient method.. though again it depends on the mob's damage output. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 917<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 8:18:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=155>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Brainstorm: How to fix PoP Mage soloability</span><hr size=1> Add a slower, and sustaining pets becomes more efficient.  Heals become more efficient, you can med longer while the pet fights.  Chaining, IMO is for times you don't have access to a slower.  There's also aggro control issues when chaining with a slower. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Poobah Goladus</span><br>  Posts: 2638<br> <font color=#333333>(2/9/03 3:25:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=156>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.