and btw just soloed a planarian larvae in plane of disease(hit for 28<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  The pet enraged and I had stepped in to take a few hits(remember doing that anyone?) but I did manage to win.  I think if I had a healinv III item or the level 60 pet heal the fight would have been won fairly easily.  Seriously, playing my mage now feels just like it did back when I was in my 20s and 30s.  Fights are a tad longer, stakes are a tad higher, and I have a few new toys but otherwise my strategy is very traditional. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=immlazen>Immlazen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#333333>(2/9/03 5:17:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=159>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Brainstorm: How to fix PoP Mage soloability</span><hr size=1> Excuse me, but Im at the point where I am &quot;VERY MUCH&quot; against chaining be a tactic to say we are on par with other soloers.<br>
